1) Build three triangles out of tiles in one corner of the map. Place the ninja among these tiles, so that he lands on a oneway at the very beginning.
2) There should be two exits.
3) Put a bounce block in the center with a mine cloud around it. Place one of the exit keys just next to the bounce block. Place a rocket anywhere.
4) Choose an edge and put some one-way walls on it. Add some well-placed mines near the exits.
5) Place two looked doors somewhere. Place a regular-ish shape of tiles near the top. Place some gold near these tiles.
6) Place three zap drones in the map somewhere. At least one should be a seeker drone. Place some obstacles so the drones steadily migrate.
7) Place two EDITED launch pads anywhere. One must increase the ninjas mobility, the other must decrease it.
8) There should be two thwumps in the map. They must be in unrelated sections. These thwumps should be as helpful to the ninja as possible.
9) Place gold where-ever needed.

That's not the solution I intended (dangling N down the side of the pit to draw them all together) but that's what I love about N. There is always another way!

Intended solution:

Pit 1: Jump into the middle of the pit and quickly jump out. Now you can get each switch with a swift movement.

Pit 2: Jump and land where the switch is. Jump again very quickly!

Pit 3 (top right): Just jump the entire pit. Helps if you get some momentum by walljumping off the structure on the left

Pit 4 (top left): Jump into the pit and land inbetween the two floorguards you can get to from there. Again, you'll need to jump very quickly out of the pit. You can then pass under the stalactite with a swift motion.

Maybe I should do a redux to force this method? :)
